27 Dec 2019 15:02






Nice and cute! I love the idea, and I really like how paired down you kept the information. Just enough for us to know what it does and how it fits into a story.

You have a couple of awkward sentences, but nothing that breaks the story. EX:



SCP-4657 is a wooden box housing a single mechanical button. The exterior of the box is composed of common mahogany wood and is otherwise unremarkable aside from a set of instructions engraved on one of the faces.
附加记录：    

Could be written as:



SCP-4657 is a box made of mahogany wood that houses a single mechanical button. There is a set of instructions engraved into one of the faces.
附加记录：    

+block

–block


The way you have it, you're telling us that it's wooden twice. And in general, you never need to tell anybody that something is unremarkable. Unless is anomalously unremarkable (which would be cool as hell but definitely not what you're going for). And I don't know if we even need to know that it's made of mahogany, but that's entirely up to you.

You also have this:



The fireworks will not leave behind any residue or burn marks, nor will they cause any harmful visual or auditory effects.
附加记录：    

Which is stating this as absolute fact. It will do this. But it's hard to know those things for sure with an anomalous object. You could try:



The fireworks have not been observed to leave behind any residue of burn marks, nor have they caused any harmful visual or auditory effects.
附加记录：    

Some of that is stylistic choice. And obviously, you should write in your own voice. This is a good article, and it stands perfectly well without any changes. But those sorts of phrasing issues are definitely something to keep in mind going forward.

Thanks for the fun article. I love seeing SCPs that aren't all grimdark.





